The paper deals with pursuit-evasion using multiple Autonomous Underwater Vehicles (AUVs) in a 3D water volume, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm proposed for range limited sensing in 3D environments involves decision-making and planning, which are key areas of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of multiple AUVs also involves coordination and control, which are areas of systems and control (cs.SY). The algorithm involves optimization of the cage formation, which can be considered as a mathematical optimization problem (cs.MA). Finally, the paper also involves computer vision techniques for sensing and tracking the evader, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV).
